Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.87,0:00:05.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has returned to Heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.46,0:00:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All that remains of Richard Brawn is an empty shell.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.15,0:00:14.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His soul shall live on forever in eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.99,0:00:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us swear to his soul that we will live on with hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.46,0:00:28.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us open our Bibles to Psalm 23.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.42,0:00:30.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is too much...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.88,0:00:34.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a sad funeral...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.22,0:00:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was an outstanding detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.18,0:00:40.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...yet not one of his colleagues came to his funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.35,0:00:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He caused a lot of problems by drinking on the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.23,0:00:47.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eventually, he fell to his death, totally drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.52,0:00:50.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what the police said, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.49,0:00:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard Richard was supposed to meet with \N his daughter the day after he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.56,0:01:04.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.37,0:01:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did I do for him?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.38,0:01:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Reichwein...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.05,0:01:14.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just sat there and listened to his story, \N then told him he had recovered!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.43,0:01:20.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was I able to do for him?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.10,0:01:24.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.19,0:01:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we can find him, we may be able \N to find out what really happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.86,0:01:30.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.17,0:01:32.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think it's strange, Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.92,0:01:36.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was no accident, nor was it suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.39,0:01:40.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Richard was on the phone talking with his \N daughter just a few hours before he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.54,0:01:43.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were to meet the next day...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.75,0:01:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor, you did everything you could for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.67,0:01:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Richard really did recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.51,0:02:01.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't blame yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.77,0:03:37.99,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(322,0)\pos(358,346)}A Decision
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.05,0:03:43.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to this, Doc...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.01,0:03:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since I found out about his affair, \N he hasn't said a word to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.81,0:03:54.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Day after day, he just washes the \N car, then mows the lawn...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.15,0:03:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He won't even look at me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.80,0:04:00.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's better than when he didn't bother coming home...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.28,0:04:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but if this continues, I might go crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.49,0:04:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you listening, Doc?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.74,0:04:09.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah, please continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.68,0:04:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when I went to that woman's place...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.79,0:04:16.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...what do you think happened, Doc?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.18,0:04:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Murder?  No, that was simply an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.10,0:04:33.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That night Richard Brawn went up to the roof of Building \N #12 at the University of Munich by himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.06,0:04:37.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...downed a bottle of whiskey, and \N fell to his death, dead drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.07,0:04:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bottle... did you follow up on that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.19,0:04:45.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, and Richard's fingerprints were all over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.45,0:04:48.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I see that bottle?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.33,0:04:51.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well.. sure, but it's broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.67,0:04:58.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Richard...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.20,0:05:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think it's strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.66,0:05:18.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Richard was on the phone talking with his \N daughter just a few hours before he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.15,0:05:21.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were to meet the next day...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.30,0:05:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, this guy was definitely here that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.26,0:05:49.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was he alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.51,0:05:52.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.68,0:05:57.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you know he was here, but you don't \N remember if he was with anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.44,0:05:59.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he only ordered coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.48,0:06:01.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.57,0:06:05.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's rare for someone to order coffee here at that hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.95,0:06:13.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was this young man with him at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.21,0:06:16.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.96,0:06:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, try to remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.12,0:06:19.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.71,0:06:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A lot of customers are always coming and going.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.30,0:06:25.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's true that he bought a bottle of whiskey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.51,0:06:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's written on the bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.47,0:06:29.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did Richard really buy that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.89,0:06:31.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.89,0:06:35.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bill just says "Racke, one bottle."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.43,0:06:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you just say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.28,0:06:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Racke, one bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.16,0:06:58.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't I notice that when I saw \N the label at the police station?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.08,0:06:58.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.93,0:07:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you been drinking again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.97,0:07:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.89,0:07:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.43,0:07:07.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you have?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.64,0:07:09.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whiskey.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.39,0:07:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only ever drink whiskey.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.31,0:07:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.90,0:07:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're filling the room with the smell of Racke.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.15,0:07:16.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Racke?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.23,0:07:17.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you kidding?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.78,0:07:20.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd never drink such vile domestic whiskey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.15,0:07:22.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only drink genuine Scotch whiskey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.61,0:07:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing else!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.54,0:07:30.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Richard didn't buy that whiskey.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.51,0:07:45.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Johan...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.43,0:07:49.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.82,0:07:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.88,0:07:59.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.46,0:08:54.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.44,0:08:56.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.58,0:08:58.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you try to push me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.79,0:09:01.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.17,0:09:02.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't play innocent!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.34,0:09:05.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.59,0:09:07.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, pops.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.51,0:09:09.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You need something from my friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.89,0:09:16.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Die, bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.74,0:09:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who wanted you to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.29,0:09:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Consider your age.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.95,0:09:38.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An old man is better off taking care of his grandkids.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.54,0:09:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, w-wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.05,0:09:44.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.27,0:09:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to be in the border police.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.42,0:10:02.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you try to push me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.19,0:10:03.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.94,0:10:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't underestimate a former police officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.74,0:10:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone asked me to...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.41,0:10:10.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who asked?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.22,0:10:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A big guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.76,0:10:14.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A big guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.62,0:10:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw this big guy in the subway.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.83,0:10:21.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He gave me some money to push you off the platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.22,0:11:13.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bought this for you, Richard.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.80,0:11:16.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's genuine Scotch.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.51,0:11:17.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted a drink, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.27,0:11:26.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.40,0:11:29.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drink as much as you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.78,0:11:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Richard, leave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.70,0:11:42.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll definitely figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.37,0:11:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.25,0:11:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Johan is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.75,0:12:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Doc.  I told my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.71,0:12:09.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Your habit of having affairs is like a disease."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.51,0:12:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Why don't you see a doctor and get some counseling?"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.35,0:12:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doc, are you listening to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.52,0:12:20.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.58,0:12:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course, Mrs. Hesse.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.38,0:12:24.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.84,0:12:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not changing, so I'm only \N going to get more depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.09,0:12:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not really depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.20,0:12:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.37,0:12:42.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rather, I'm more concerned about you husband, silently \N washing the car and mowing the lawn every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.71,0:12:43.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think so, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.92,0:12:46.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.34,0:12:50.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doc, please, could you see him?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.67,0:12:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.76,0:12:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.18,0:12:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about 5 PM the day after tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.85,0:12:58.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll ask him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.31,0:13:05.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Smack some sense into the big oaf!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.45,0:13:23.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor, was she the last patient for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.92,0:13:27.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then you can go home, Mehres.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.54,0:13:28.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.88,0:13:33.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Mehres, you forgot to lock \N the back door yesterday, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.38,0:13:36.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.09,0:13:37.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I almost forgot to do it today, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.68,0:13:39.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I did it again...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.60,0:13:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.78,0:13:56.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?  Dr. Gillen?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.34,0:13:58.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.49,0:14:00.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw it in the newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.75,0:14:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your advertisement.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.90,0:14:08.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Let's reminisce about our cheating.  Rudi."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.71,0:14:14.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will Dr. Tenma really contact us because of this ad?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.76,0:14:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, if Tenma reads it, he will.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.60,0:14:22.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only he and I know what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.06,0:14:24.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.02,0:14:28.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor, please don't do anything \N reckless before he shows up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.15,0:14:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.56,0:14:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there is one thing I need to find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.15,0:14:34.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.44,0:14:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a prostitute who impersonated Margot Langer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.28,0:14:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Richard told me about her...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.49,0:14:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a young man with Fahren, the boy who \N committed suicide, when he went to see that woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.46,0:14:49.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A handsome young man with blond hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.86,0:14:54.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please be careful, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.57,0:14:56.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.17,0:15:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be careful, so I'll be able to figure out everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.35,0:15:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For Richard's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.39,0:15:06.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get in touch with you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.16,0:15:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mehres...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.68,0:15:24.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You forgot to close the window today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.29,0:15:30.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Margot Langer?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.77,0:15:31.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't know her
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.94,0:15:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think she currently goes by \N the name of Sofie something...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.00,0:15:40.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that fat old woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.01,0:15:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is she your kind of girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.63,0:15:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm not like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.05,0:15:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no need to be shy at your age.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.14,0:15:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn at the second corner, and she's on \N the second floor of the old building.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.68,0:15:51.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.69,0:15:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's not there, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.48,0:15:54.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.19,0:15:56.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't seen her lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.31,0:15:58.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess she's gone somewhere nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.94,0:16:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Somewhere nice?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.15,0:16:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, why on earth is that fat old woman so popular?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.82,0:16:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard an incredibly rich man used \N to come by her place until recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.41,0:16:10.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did she go?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.87,0:16:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, how about me, gramps?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.79,0:16:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you a much better time than \N that old woman ever would.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.92,0:16:19.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know where she went?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.25,0:16:20.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.92,0:16:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe she went somewhere with the new guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.88,0:16:25.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The new guy/
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.01,0:16:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, she was all over him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.22,0:16:31.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a big guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.06,0:16:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A big guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.98,0:16:37.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looked like he was big down there, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.94,0:16:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor, can I leave for today?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.36,0:16:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah, you work til 5 PM today, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.83,0:16:54.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only other patient for today is the \N unfaithful husband, so it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.16,0:16:55.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you have a date, Mehres?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.12,0:16:57.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.09,0:17:01.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't forget to lock up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.68,0:17:11.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I show this picture to Sofie, the Margot Langer \N impersonator, and if she confirms that...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.68,0:17:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the young man who was with Fahren was indeed Johan...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.60,0:17:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'm one step closer to the truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.28,0:17:25.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.36,0:17:27.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Hesse, my wife made an appointment for me today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.24,0:17:31.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.37,0:17:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should I try visiting that woman's place again tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.63,0:17:43.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please to meet you, Dr. Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.11,0:17:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you too, Mr. Hesse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.01,0:17:46.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.74,0:17:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.89,0:17:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never been to see a counselor before, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.31,0:17:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to be nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.72,0:17:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please relax, and talk about anything you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.73,0:18:04.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever you say here will stay strictly confidential \N between you and me, so please don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.53,0:18:06.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even to my wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.36,0:18:07.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.61,0:18:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How have you been recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.76,0:18:13.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you worried about anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.99,0:18:15.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Worried?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.33,0:18:15.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.87,0:18:21.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My wife found out that I was having an affair.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.38,0:18:24.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.17,0:18:26.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So when I'm at home, I don't know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.92,0:18:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mow the lawn, or wash my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.09,0:18:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every day passes like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.30,0:18:35.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do those things make you feel better?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.60,0:18:36.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.89,0:18:40.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't talk to my wife at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.48,0:18:43.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean, even though you want to \N talk, you don't know where to start?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.69,0:18:46.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.90,0:18:48.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the other woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.90,0:18:50.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.36,0:18:53.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The woman you're having an affair with...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.78,0:18:56.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.41,0:18:57.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.83,0:19:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I dreamt that I killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.88,0:19:04.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have that kind of dream often?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.71,0:19:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Often?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.50,0:19:10.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I haven't had it lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.80,0:19:14.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.10,0:19:21.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you had an affair.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.40,0:19:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, since I met him...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.07,0:19:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Him?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.28,0:19:32.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A handsome young man with blond hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.83,0:19:39.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I killed lots of people, or \N even if this country collapsed...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.41,0:19:43.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...everything was like a dream to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.54,0:19:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But since I met him, things have changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.71,0:19:54.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything seems so real, and I'm no longer lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.56,0:20:07.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Would you like some tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.90,0:20:11.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.09,0:20:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a little thirsty.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.32,0:20:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you excuse me for a minute, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.62,0:20:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My secretary went home already.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.13,0:20:27.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that she had a date.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.42,0:20:37.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She makes really good tea, but I'm \N afraid I won't be able to serve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.73,0:20:45.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.81,0:20:47.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.86,0:20:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With this kind of career, you must go through a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.32,0:20:55.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Getting to know people's dreams...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.16,0:21:03.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no good if you learn of dreams you shouldn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.59,0:21:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially the fact that I'm a murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.39,0:21:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Anyway, if you and your wife \N want to start over together...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.78,0:21:30.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you should start by talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.03,0:21:35.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, I hope you forgot to lock the back door, Mehres!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.94,0:22:13.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You...!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.36,0:22:16.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quickly, run!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.16,0:22:18.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.66,0:22:21.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been watching you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.64,0:22:23.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're being targeted!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.54,0:22:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.67,0:22:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
